Innovate With The Cloud Built For Cognitive Business

Ram Vennam (IBM Bluemix Developer Advocate)

background:
A discussion about open source software for creating private and public cloud solutions in three different ways.
    
With Prashant Bhuyan (Co-Founder, CTO/CDO, Alpha Modus)

subtitle: Open Cloud Everywhere
biography: VP of Cloud Architecture and Technology, IBM
background:
Angel Diaz hosts a panel with leaders from across the open source community about the growth and momentum of open and how it is being applied to address the unique needs of the enterprise, particularly around hybrid.

Chip Childers (Technology Chief of Staff, Cloud Foundry)
Jason McGee (IBM Fellow, VP and CTO, Cloud Foundation Services)
Jesse Proudman (CTO, Blue Box)
Mary Mt. Pleasant (Senior Cloud Advisor, IBM)

title: Analyst Keynote
subtitle: Cloud Is All About The Customer

Analyst Keynote, New Research: Cloud Is All About The Customer 
    
Debuting new research data, John Rymer discusses the rapid growth of 'customer-centric' workloads in the cloud and the challenges many organizations have faced with private cloud.

title: Presentation
subtitle: Enterprise Digital Transformation
background:

Jyoti Chawla (Senior Cloud Advisor, IBM)

title: Platform Track
subtitle: Modern Enterprise Apps
biography: IBM Fellow, VP and CTO, Cloud Foundation Services
background:
Modern Enterprise Apps are Powered by Hybrid Cloud From bare metal to elastic runtimes. On-prem to off-prem. Multi-tenant to single. The cloud is a place of multitudes. In this session Bala and Jason will discuss the patterns of adoption and architecture that represent how companies are constructing next generation solutions.
    
Moe Abdula (VP of Cloud Foundational Services, IBM)    
Bala Rajaraman (CTO and IBM Fellow, Cloud Platform Services, IBM)

title: Data Track
subtitle: Open For Data
background: Open For Data Modern Apps And Services are leveraging data to change the way we engage with users in a more personalized way. Skyla Loomis talks big data, analytics, NoSQL, SQL and how IBM Cloud is open for data.

title: Platform Track
subtitle: Expect More From Private Cloud
background:
Cloud is not a piece of technology. Cloud is an experience, an SLA and an API. In this session, Bala, Jeff and Jesse will discuss new ways of delivering cloud as-a-service, but within the enterprise data center. 
    
Jeff Brent (Technical Product Manager - IBM Cloud)
Jesse Proudman (CTO, Blue Box)

title: Data Track
subtitle: New Data Sources, New Value.
background:
New Data Sources, New Value. Watson, Weather and Beyond This discussion led by Michael Karasick delves into how data from weather, sensors, text and images can be used to change the way apps interact with users and machines.  
    
Tim Vanderham (VP of Development, Next Generation Platform)
Jesse Proudman (CTO of Blue Box)
